HEADWORD: Psoriasis
<hw>Pso*ri"a*sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/, fr. <?/ psora.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The state
of being affected with psora.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>A cutaneous disease, characterized by imbricated silvery scales,
affecting only the superficial layers of the skin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

